FBIS4-38359 "drsov104_a_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-104 Daily Report 31 May 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Strategic Missile Forces Cited on Missile Retargeting Strategic Missile Forces Cited on Missile Retargeting PM3005161194 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 31 May 94 p 1 PM3005161194 Moscow IZVESTIYA Russian BFN [Viktor Litovkin report: "Russian Strategic Missiles No Longer Threaten United States and Britain"] [Text] As of 30 May 1994 none of Russia's more than 1,000 strategic missiles on alert duty in silos, on submarines, and on road-mobile launchers are targeted against any installations on the territory of the United States and Britain, IZVESTIYA was told by the Strategic Missile Forces [SMF] Press Center. The missiles have been retargeted in line with Russian-U.S. and Russian-British accords and also in connection with the Russian president's directive, the military said. According to them, the SMF have formulated and implemented special measures to organize the daily activity and lives of the troops with untargeted missiles. At the same time missilemen have given assurances that the missile units' combat readiness remains at the same high level.
